    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1039"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–2154</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Declaration by the Royal Government of Laos</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Reference: Article 3 of the Final Declaration</hi>)<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1039fn1">This declaration was also printed in Cmd. 9239, p. 41 and
                        in <hi rend="italic">Conférence de Genève</hi>, p. 461.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <gloss target="#t_IC1">IC</gloss>/45 Rev. 1</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-21">21 July
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Royal Government of Laos,</p>
                <p>In the desire to ensure harmony and agreement among the peoples of the
                    Kingdom,</p>
                <p>Declares itself resolved to take the necessary measures to integrate all
                    citizens, without discrimination, into the national community and <pb
                        facs="1569" n="1543" xml:id="pg_1543"/> to guarantee them the enjoyment of
                    the rights and freedoms for which the Constitution of the Kingdom provides;</p>
                <p>Affirms that all Laotian citizens may freely participate as electors or
                    candidates in general elections by secret ballot;</p>
                <p>Announces, furthermore, that it will promulgate measures to provide for special
                    representation in the Royal Administration of the provinces of Phang Saly and
                    Sam Neua during the interval between the cessation of hostilities and the
                    general elections of the interests of Laotian nationals who did not support the
                    Royal forces during hostilities.</p>
            </div>
